206 template<typename DataType_, int k_ = 1>
207 class SineTensorStatic
208 {
209 static_assert(k_ > 0, "parameter k_ must be a positive integer");
210
211 public:
213 static DataType_ kpi()
214 {
215 return DataType_(k_) * Math::pi<DataType_>();
216 }
217
219 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x)
220 {
221 return Math::sin(kpi() * x);
222 }
223
225 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
226 {
227 return Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y);
228 }
229
231 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
232 {
233 return Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
234 }
235
237 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x)
238 {
239 return kpi() * Math::cos(kpi() * x);
240 }
241
243 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
244 {
245 return kpi() * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y);
246 }
247
249 static DataType_ der_y(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
250 {
251 return kpi() * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y);
252 }
253
255 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
256 {
257 return kpi() * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
258 }
259
261 static DataType_ der_y(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
262 {
263 return kpi() * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
264 }
265
267 static DataType_ der_z(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
268 {
269 return kpi() * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::cos(kpi() * z);
270 }
271
273 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x)
274 {
275 return -Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::sin(kpi() * x);
276 }
277
279 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
280 {

287 return der_xx(x, y);

293 return Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y);
294 }
295
297 static DataType_ der_yx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
298 {
299 return der_xy(x, y);
300 }
301
303 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
304 {
305 return -Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);

307

312 }

580 template<typename DataType_>
581 class ExpBubbleScalarStatic
582 {
583 public:
585 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x)
586 {
587 return (Math::exp(-Math::sqr(DataType_(2)*x - DataType_(1))) - Math::exp(-DataType_(1))) / (DataType_(1) - Math::exp(-DataType_(1)));
588 }
589
591 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x)
592 {
593 return (DataType_(8)*x - DataType_(4))*Math::exp(-Math::sqr(DataType_(2)*x - DataType_(1))) / (Math::exp(-DataType_(1)) - DataType_(1));
594 }
595
597 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x)
598 {
599 return (DataType_(64)*x*(DataType_(1)-x)-DataType_(8)) * Math::exp(-Math::sqr(DataType_(2)*x - DataType_(1))) / (Math::exp(-DataType_(1)) - DataType_(1));
600 }
601 }; // class ExpBubbleScalarStatic<...>

857 template<int dim_, typename DataType_>
858 class DistanceFunction :
859 public Analytic::Function
860 {
861 public:
862 static constexpr int domain_dim = dim_;
863 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
864 static constexpr bool can_value = true;
865 static constexpr bool can_grad = true;
866 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
867
868 typedef Tiny::Vector<DataType_, dim_> PointType;
869
871 template<typename EvalTraits_>
872 class Evaluator :
873 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
874 {
875 public:
877 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
879 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
881 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
883 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
885 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
886
887 private:
889 const PointType _origin;
890
891 public:
893 explicit Evaluator(const DistanceFunction& function) :
894 _origin(function._origin)
895 {
896 }
897
898 ValueType value(const PointType& point) const
899 {
900 return (point - _origin).norm_euclid();
901 }
902
903 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
904 {
905 DataType norm (this->value(point));
906
907 if(norm < Math::eps<DataType>())
908 return GradientType::null();
909
910 return (DataType(1) / norm) * (point - _origin);
911 }
912
913 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
914 {
915 DataType norm (this->value(point));
916 if(norm < Math::eps<DataType>())
917 return HessianType::null();
918
919 HessianType hess (DataType(0));
920 norm = DataType(1)/norm;
921 DataType denom = Math::sqr(norm)*norm;
922
923 for(int i(0); i < dim_; ++i)
924 {
925 hess[i][i] = norm;
926 for(int j(0); j < dim_; ++j)
927 {
928 hess[i][j] -= ((point[i] - _origin[i]) * (point[j] - _origin[j]))*denom;
929 }
930 }
931 return hess;
932 }
933 }; // class DistanceFunction::Evaluator<...>
934
935 public:
937 PointType _origin;
938
939 public:
941 explicit DistanceFunction(const PointType& origin) :
942 _origin(origin)
943 {
944 }
945
947 void set_point(const PointType& origin)
948 {
949 _origin = origin;
950 }
951 }; // class DistanceFunction

969 template<int dim_, typename DataType_>
970 class DistanceFunctionSD :
971 public Analytic::Function
972 {
973 public:
974 static constexpr int domain_dim = dim_;
975 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
976
977 static constexpr bool can_value = true;
978 static constexpr bool can_grad = true;
979 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
980
981 typedef Tiny::Vector<DataType_, dim_> PointType;
982
984 template<typename EvalTraits_>
985 class Evaluator :
986 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
987 {
988 public:
990 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
992 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
994 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
996 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
998 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
999
1000 private:
1002 const PointType _origin;
1004 const DataType _a, _b;
1005
1006 public:
1008 explicit Evaluator(const DistanceFunctionSD& function) :
1009 _origin(function._origin),
1010 _a(function._a),
1011 _b(function._b)
1012 {
1013 }
1014
1015 ValueType value(const PointType& point) const
1016 {
1017 return _a + _b*(point - _origin).norm_euclid();
1018 }
1019
1020 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
1021 {
1022 DataType norm ((point - _origin).norm_euclid());
1023 if(norm < Math::eps<DataType>())
1024 return GradientType::null();
1025
1026 return (_b / norm) * (point - _origin);
1027 }
1028
1029 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
1030 {
1031 DataType norm ((point - _origin).norm_euclid());
1032 if(norm <= Math::eps<DataType>())
1033 return HessianType::null();
1034
1035 HessianType hess(DataType(0));
1036
1037 norm = DataType(1)/norm;
1038 DataType denom = _b*Math::sqr(norm)*norm;
1039
1040 for(int i(0); i < dim_; ++i)
1041 {
1042 hess[i][i] = _b*norm;
1043 for(int j(0); j < dim_; ++j)
1044 {

1572 template<typename DataType_>
1573 class PolynomialFunction1D :
1574 public Analytic::Function
1575 {
1576 public:
1578 static constexpr int domain_dim = 1;
1580 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
1582 static constexpr bool can_value = true;
1584 static constexpr bool can_grad = true;
1586 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
1587
1589 template<typename EvalTraits_>
1590 class Evaluator :
1591 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
1592 {
1593 public:
1594 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
1595 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
1596 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
1597 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
1598 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
1599
1600 private:
1602 std::vector<DataType> _coeff;
1603
1604 public:
1606 explicit Evaluator(const PolynomialFunction1D& function)
1607 {
1608 for(auto it = function._coeff.begin(); it != function._coeff.end(); ++it)
1609 _coeff.push_back(DataType(*it));
1610 }
1611
1612 ValueType value(const PointType& point) const
1613 {
1614 // evaluate polynomial via horner scheme
1615 DataType x = point[0];
1616 DataType y = DataType(0);
1617 for(std::size_t k(_coeff.size()); k > std::size_t(0); )
1618 y = x * y + _coeff[--k];
1619
1620 return y;
1621 }
1622
1623 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
1624 {
1625 std::size_t k = _coeff.size();
1626 if(k <= std::size_t(0))
1627 return GradientType::null();
1628
1629 // evaluate polynomial via horner scheme
1630 DataType x = point[0];
1631 DataType y = DataType(0);
1632 for( ; (--k) > std::size_t(0); )
1633 y = x * y + (_coeff[k] * DataType(k));
1634
1635 return GradientType(y);
1636 }
1637
1638 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
1639 {
1640 std::size_t k = _coeff.size();
1641 if(k <= std::size_t(1))
1642 return HessianType::null();
1643
1644 // evaluate polynomial via horner scheme
1645 DataType x = point[0];
1646 DataType y = DataType(0);
1647 for( ; (--k) > std::size_t(1); )
1648 y = x * y + (_coeff[k] * DataType(k*(k-1)));
1649
1650 return HessianType(y);
1651 }
1652 }; // class PolynomialFunction1D::Evaluator
1653
1654 private:
1656 std::vector<DataType_> _coeff;
1657
1658 public:
1660 PolynomialFunction1D() :
1661 _coeff()
1662 {
1663 }
1664
1671 explicit PolynomialFunction1D(std::initializer_list<DataType_> coeff) :
1672 _coeff(coeff)
1673 {
1674 }
1675
1688 Index set_coeff(Index degree, DataType_ coeff)
1689 {
1690 // check degree
1691 if(Index(_coeff.size()) <= degree)
1692 _coeff.resize(std::size_t(degree+1), DataType_(0));
1693
1694 // set coefficient
1695 _coeff.at(std::size_t(degree)) = coeff;
1696
1697 // return degree+1
1698 return Index(_coeff.size());
1699 }
1700 }; // class PolynomialFunction1D

2052 // maximum value
2053 DataType_ _vmax;
2054
2055 public:
2062 ParProfileBase() :
2063 _x0(0.0), _y0(0.0), _x1(0.0), _y1(1.0), _vmax(1.0)

2066
2079 explicit ParProfileBase(DataType_ x0, DataType_ y0, DataType_ x1, DataType_ y1, DataType_ vmax = DataType_(1.0)) :
2080 _x0(x0), _y0(y0), _x1(x1), _y1(y1), _vmax(vmax)
2081 {

2083
2101 bool parse(const String& sbc)
2102 {
2103 auto li = sbc.find_first_of('(');
2104 auto ri = sbc.find_last_of(')');
2105 if((li == sbc.npos) || (ri == sbc.npos))
2106 return false;
2107
2108 std::deque<String> sv = sbc.substr(li+1, ri-li-1).split_by_string(",");
2109 if((sv.size() < std::size_t(2)) || (sv.size() > std::size_t(3)))
2110 return false;
2111
2112 std::deque<String> sv0 = sv[0].trim().split_by_whitespaces();
2113 std::deque<String> sv1 = sv[1].trim().split_by_whitespaces();
2114 if(sv0.size() != std::size_t(2)) return false;
2115 if(sv1.size() != std::size_t(2)) return false;
2116
2117 if(!sv0[0].parse(_x0)) return false;
2118 if(!sv0[1].parse(_y0)) return false;
2119 if(!sv1[0].parse(_x1)) return false;
2120 if(!sv1[1].parse(_y1)) return false;
2121
2122 if((sv.size() == std::size_t(3)) && !sv.back().parse(_vmax))
2123 return false;
2124
2125 return true;
2126 }

2156 typedef typename Traits_::PointType PointType;
2157 typedef typename Traits_::ValueType ValueType;
2158 typedef typename Traits_::GradientType GradientType;

2160
2161 PointType _vo, _ve;
2162 DataType _den, _vmax;
2163
2164 public:
2165 explicit Evaluator(const ParProfileScalar& function)
2166 {
2167 _vo[0] = DataType(function._x0);
2168 _vo[1] = DataType(function._y0);
2169 _ve[0] = DataType(function._x1 - function._x0);
2170 _ve[1] = DataType(function._y1 - function._y0);
2171 _den = DataType(1) / Tiny::dot(_ve, _ve);
2172 _vmax = DataType(function._vmax);
2173 }
2174
2175 ValueType value(const PointType& point)
2176 {
2177 // project point onto line segment
2178 const DataType x = Math::clamp(Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den, DataType(0), DataType(1));
2179 // compute function value
2180 return _vmax * DataType(4) * x * (DataType(1) - x);
2181 }
2182
2183 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point)
2184 {
2185 // project point onto line segment
2186 const DataType x = Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den;
2187
2188 // Note: the gradient has a singularity at x=0 and x=1
2189 if((x < DataType(0)) || (x > DataType(1)))
2190 return GradientType::null();
2191
2192 return (_vmax * _den * DataType(4) * (DataType(1) - DataType(2)*x)) * _ve;
2193 }
2194
2195 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point)
2196 {
2197 // project point onto line segment
2198 const DataType x = Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den;
2199
2200 // Note: the hessian has a singularity at x=0 and x=1
2201 if((x < DataType(0)) || (x > DataType(1)))
2202 return HessianType::null();
2203
2204 HessianType hess;
2205 const DataType v = -DataType(8) * _vmax * _den * _den;
2206 hess[0][0] = v * _ve[0] * _ve[0];
2207 hess[0][1] = hess[1][0] = v * _ve[0] * _ve[1];
2208 hess[1][1] = v * _ve[1] * _ve[1];
2209 return hess;
2210 }

2300 return HessianType::null();

2539
2540 for (int d(1); d < domain_dim; ++d)
2541 {
2542 _fac *= DataType(4)/Math::sqr(_range.at(std::size_t(d-1))[1]-_range.at(std::size_t(d-1))[0]);

2567
2568 for (int q(1); q < domain_dim; ++q)
2569 {
2570 if (q != d)
2571 grad[d][0] *= (point[q] - _range.at(std::size_t(q - 1))[0]) * (_range.at(std::size_t(q - 1))[1] - point[q]);

3216 {
3217 const DataType x = point[0];
3218 const DataType y = point[1];
3219 const DataType z = point[2];
3220 const DataType re = DataType(1) / point.norm_euclid();
3221 const DataType cx = Math::cos(pi * re * x);
3222 const DataType cy = Math::cos(pi * re * y);
3223 const DataType cz = Math::cos(pi * re * z);

3225 const DataType sy = Math::sin(pi * re * y);

3228 grad[0] = +pi * Math::cub(re) * (cx*sz*sy*y*y + cx*sz*sy*z*z - sx*x*y*cy*sz - sx*sy*x*z*cz);

3230 grad[2] = -pi * Math::cub(re) * (x*z*cx*sy*sz + sx*z*y*cy*sz - sx*cz*sy*x*x - sx*cz*sy*y*y);

4259 return val;
4260
4261 const DataType x(point[0]), y(point[1]);
4262 const DataType q = DataType(1) / d;
4263 const DataType s2pdq = Math::sin(_pi2 * d) * q;

4267 val[1] = -_nu*q*x*(-_pi2*c2pdq + (_pi2*_pi2*d + q)*s2pdq) - _beta*y*s2pdq*s2pdq - _theta*x*s2pdq - _sigma*y*c2pdq;
